Pro Pascal Compiler - Version iid 3.1

Compilation of: PRINTER.PAS

Options:    LNIPJ2

    1   {**************************************************************
    2   *                                                             *
    3   * PRINTER INTERFACE ROUTINES FOR FUJITSU DL-3400 PRINTER      *
    4   *                                                             *
    5   * Contains the printer specific routines to drive a Fujitsu   *
    6   * DL-3400 printer.                                            *
    7   * The standard intalization and matinence routines are        *
    8   * implemented, plus a universal output routine.               *
    9   * The output communication is done via a two-dementional      *
   10   * buffer of pixels, which represent all the pixels the        *
   11   * printer may output in a single "line". The pixels are in    *
   12   * VGA standard 16 color codes. Utilizing the X and Y          *
   13   * dementions, ICD sizes the printout in Y to fit the printer, *
   14   * then successively "walks" the buffer across the printout,   *
   15   * from top to bottom.                                         *
   16   * Creating the (perhaps limited) output colors from the       *
   17   * VGA colors is the job of this module, which we do by        *
   18   * dithering different printer colors together.                *
   19   * The side effect of this is that a colored object must have  *
   20   * a certain minimum size to be presented correctly (two       *
   21   * pixels).                                                    *
   22   * This does not apply to black lines.                         *
   23   * ICD obeys this rule, and does not attempt to output single  *
   24   * line objects other than black.                              *
   25   *                                                             *
   26   **************************************************************}
   27   
   28   segment ptrout;
